Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Mohammed Siraj takes the last wicket and that brings an end to the Australian inning! This is a pretty good fightback from India after having a difficult Day 1 as they have claimed 7 wickets in about one and a half sessions. This is bowled back of a length and outside the off pole. Pat Cummins looks to make room by moving to the leg side and tries to slap the ball away. He ends up hitting this straight down the throat of Ajinkya Rahane at cover. Mohammed Siraj ends with four wickets and India still have some hope in this game. Australia will be disappointed in being bowled out before Tea after the position there were in when the day started.

Commentary: NO BALL! You will not believe what has just happened! Pat Cummins has bowled yet another no ball and he will miss out on yet another wicket! He gets this to angle into the stumps from outside off. Shardul Thakur gets well across the stumps and looks to flick this into the leg side. He misses the line of the ball and gets wrapped on the pads. The umpire raises his finger straight away to the appeal and Ajinkya Rahane takes the review for Shardul Thakur instantly. Replays however show that Pat Cummins has overstepped and this will be a no ball. The onfield decision is reversed and Shardul Thakur survives as it would have been the umpire's call on wickets hitting. The Indian fans have gone absolutely berserk in celebration and the Australian skipper is fuming!

Alex Carey thinks he has heard something and asks Pat Cummins to go for the review. However, the UltraeEdge shows no spike as the ball is next to the bat or the glove. The on-field decision will stand and Australia lose their review.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Another stunner by Cameron Green, this time low to his left! On a hard length, just outside off, stays on the back foot and defend this delivery. Gets surprised by the extra bounce and ends up getting an outside edge. The ball travels low towards Cameron Green at gully. He dives low to his left and takes a one-handed stunner with his left hand. Shubman Gill stands his ground and waits for the third umpire's decision. The replays show that the ball sticks in Green's grasp and stays in even as his elbow made contact with the ground. The Aussies are delighted as they break a flourishing opening stand. That will also be Tea on Day 4!

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Poor shot selection by Rohit Sharma and it has cost him his wicket! Nathan Lyon strikes in his first over as it took him 5 balls to make an impact and this is what the Australians needed to pick themselves up on the field. Nathan Lyon tosses this full and in line with the stumps. Rohit Sharma looks to go for the sweep but misses and gets hit flush on the pad. Nathan Lyon goes up in appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Rohit Sharma reviews this and UltraEdge shows that there is no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows three red and the Indian skipper has to depart as they lose a review as well. India lose their second wicket just when this partnership was looking good. Virat Kohli is the new man in.
